Other REST API endpoints

Source: vignettes/sc_info.Rmd
sc_info.Rmd

Apart form /table and /schema, there is also support for the simple endpoints /info and /rate_limit.

sc_info()
  locale displayName
1     de     Deutsch
2     en     English
sc_rate_limit_table()
## remaining: 100/100
## reset:     2021-08-13 14:37:12

Rate limits can also be obtained from the response of the /table endpoint with $rate_limit.

table <- sc_table(sc_example("population_timeseries.json"))
table$rate_limit
## remaining: 99/100
## reset:     2021-08-11 13:52:43

STATcube uses caching for the /table endpoint by default. If the same request to sc_table() is sent several times, this will not count towards the rate-limit (100 requests per hour).
